text: Archbishop Sebouh Chouldjian (born Haik Sarkis Chouldjian; March 24, 1959 - November 19, 2020) was a Turkish-born Armenian Apostolic prelate. He was the Archbishop of the Diocese of Gougark from 1996 until his death. He was born in Malatya, Turkey. Chouldjian died of COVID-19 on November 19, 2020 in Yerevan, Armenia at the age of 61. ==References== Category:1959 births Category:2020 deaths Category:Deaths from the COVID-19 pandemic in Armenia Category:Turkish Christian clergy Category:Armenian Christian clergy Category:Oriental Orthodox Christians Category:Patriarchs
